subSubSection.paragraph:
Pulitzer-Finali (1993)
reported 

Sigmadocia flagellifer

from deeper water (
117–138 m
) off the coast of 
Kenya
. Oxeas were somewhat larger (310–370 × 13–17 μm), but flagellosigmas and the larger normal sigmas were similar in size. No mention was made of a smaller sigma category, rendering conspecificity uncertain. However, as the specimen also encrusted a sponge (

Asteropus

), this material has more similarities than differences.
